.TH LRM 1 "January 2025" "lrm 0.6.12" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lrm \- Linux-native CLI tool for managing .NET .resx localization files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lrm
[\fIGLOBAL OPTIONS\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR
[\fICOMMAND OPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B LRM
(Localization Resource Manager) is a powerful, Linux-native command-line tool for managing .NET .resx localization files with an interactive Terminal UI.
.PP
Features include:
.IP \(bu 2
Interactive Terminal UI for visual editing
.IP \(bu 2
Machine translation support (Google, DeepL, OpenAI, Claude, Ollama)
.IP \(bu 2
CI/CD automation workflows
.IP \(bu 2
Validation and placeholder checking
.IP \(bu 2
Code scanning for unused/missing keys
.IP \(bu 2
Backup system with diff view
.IP \(bu 2
Multi-platform support (Linux x64/ARM64)
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to Resources folder (default: current directory)
.TP
.BR \-\-config\-file " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to configuration file (optional, default: auto-discover lrm.json)
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help information
.SH COMMANDS
.SS validate
Validate resource files for missing translations, duplicates, and errors.
.PP
.B lrm validate
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
[\fB\-\-missing\-only\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: table (default), json, simple
.TP
.BR \-\-missing\-only
Show only missing translations
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-backup
Skip automatic backup before validation
.SS stats
Display translation statistics and coverage.
.PP
.B lrm stats
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: table (default), json, simple
.SS view
View details of a specific key or pattern across all languages.
.PP
.B lrm view
\fIKEY_PATTERN\fR
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
[\fB\-\-cultures\fR \fICULTURES\fR]
[\fB\-\-search\-in\fR \fISCOPE\fR]
[\fB\-\-status\fR \fISTATUS\fR]
[\fB\-\-keys\-only\fR]
[\fB\-\-count\fR]
[\fB\-\-sort\fR]
[\fB\-\-not\fR \fIPATTERN\fR]
.TP
.I KEY_PATTERN
Key name or regex pattern (e.g., "SaveButton", "Error.*", "*.Text")
.TP
.BR \-\-search\-in " " \fISCOPE\fR
Search scope: keys (default), values, comments, both
.TP
.BR \-\-cultures " " \fICULTURES\fR
Comma-separated list of cultures to display
.TP
.BR \-\-status " " \fISTATUS\fR
Filter by translation status: translated, untranslated, all (default)
.SS add
Add a new key to all language files.
.PP
.B lrm add
\fIKEY\fR
[\fB\-i\fR|\fB\-\-interactive\fR]
[\fB\-\-lang\fR \fICULTURE\fR:\fIVALUE\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.I KEY
The key name to add
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interactive
Interactive mode (prompts for values in all languages)
.TP
.BR \-\-lang " " \fICULTURE\fR:\fIVALUE\fR
Specify value for a specific language (can be repeated)
.SS update
Update values for an existing key.
.PP
.B lrm update
\fIKEY\fR
[\fB\-\-lang\fR \fICULTURE\fR:\fIVALUE\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.SS delete
Delete a key from all language files.
.PP
.B lrm delete
\fIKEY\fR
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Skip confirmation prompt
.SS merge\-duplicates
Merge duplicate key occurrences into a single entry.
.PP
.B lrm merge\-duplicates
\fIKEY\fR
[\fB\-\-auto\-merge\fR]
[\fB\-\-keep\fR \fIINDEX\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.SS export
Export translations to CSV, JSON, or text format.
.PP
.B lrm export
[\fB\-o\fR \fIFILE\fR]
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Output file path (default: Resources.csv)
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Export format: csv (default), json, text
.SS import
Import translations from CSV file.
.PP
.B lrm import
\fIFILE\fR
[\fB\-\-validate\-after\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-validate\-after
Run validation after import
.SS edit
Launch interactive Terminal UI editor.
.PP
.B lrm edit
[\fB\-\-source\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-source\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to source code directory for code scanning (default: parent directory of resource path)
.PP
Keyboard shortcuts:
.IP \(bu 2
↑/↓ or j/k - Navigate keys
.IP \(bu 2
Enter - Edit selected key
.IP \(bu 2
Ctrl+N - Add new key
.IP \(bu 2
Del - Delete key
.IP \(bu 2
Ctrl+T - Translate selected key
.IP \(bu 2
F4 - Translate all missing
.IP \(bu 2
F5 - Configure providers
.IP \(bu 2
F6 - Validation
.IP \(bu 2
F7 - Code scan / Backup manager
.IP \(bu 2
Space - Toggle row selection
.IP \(bu 2
Ctrl+A - Select all visible keys
.IP \(bu 2
Shift+↑/↓ - Extend selection
.IP \(bu 2
Esc - Clear selection
.IP \(bu 2
Ctrl+Z/Y - Undo/Redo
.IP \(bu 2
Ctrl+C/V - Copy/Paste value
.IP \(bu 2
Ctrl+S - Save changes
.IP \(bu 2
Ctrl+Q - Quit
.SS add\-language
Create a new language file.
.PP
.B lrm add\-language
\fB\-\-culture\fR \fICULTURE\fR
[\fB\-\-copy\-from\fR \fISOURCE\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-culture " " \fICULTURE\fR
Culture code (e.g., fr, de, es)
.TP
.BR \-\-copy\-from " " \fISOURCE\fR
Copy values from source culture (default: default)
.SS remove\-language
Delete a language file.
.PP
.B lrm remove\-language
\fB\-\-culture\fR \fICULTURE\fR
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.SS list\-languages
List all detected language files.
.PP
.B lrm list\-languages
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
.SS backup list
List all backup versions.
.PP
.B lrm backup list
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
[\fB\-\-limit\fR \fIN\fR]
.SS backup create
Create a manual backup.
.PP
.B lrm backup create
[\fB\-\-description\fR \fIDESC\fR]
.SS backup restore
Restore from a backup version.
.PP
.B lrm backup restore
\fB\-\-version\fR \fIN\fR
[\fB\-\-preview\fR]
[\fB\-\-keys\fR \fIKEYS\fR]
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
.SS backup diff
Compare two backup versions or current state.
.PP
.B lrm backup diff
\fB\-\-version\fR \fIN\fR
[\fB\-\-compare\-to\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
.SS backup info
View backup metadata and statistics.
.PP
.B lrm backup info
\fB\-\-version\fR \fIN\fR
.SS backup prune
Clean up old backup versions.
.PP
.B lrm backup prune
[\fB\-\-keep\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB\-\-older\-than\fR \fIDAYS\fR]
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
.SS scan
Scan source code for localization key usage.
.PP
.B lrm scan
[\fB\-\-source\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-resource\-classes\fR \fICLASSES\fR]
[\fB\-\-localization\-methods\fR \fIMETHODS\fR]
[\fB\-\-strict\fR]
[\fB\-\-show\-unused\fR]
[\fB\-\-show\-missing\fR]
[\fB\-\-exclude\fR \fIPATTERN\fR]
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-source\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to source code (default: parent directory)
.TP
.BR \-\-resource\-classes " " \fICLASSES\fR
Comma-separated resource class names
.TP
.BR \-\-strict
High-confidence static references only
.SS translate
Automatically translate keys using machine translation.
.PP
.B lrm translate
[\fB\-\-provider\fR \fIPROVIDER\fR]
[\fB\-\-target\-languages\fR \fILANGS\fR]
[\fB\-\-only\-missing\fR]
[\fB\-\-keys\fR \fIKEYS\fR]
[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-provider " " \fIPROVIDER\fR
Translation provider: google, deepl, libretranslate, azure, openai, claude, azureopenai, ollama
.TP
.BR \-\-target\-languages " " \fILANGS\fR
Comma-separated target language codes
.TP
.BR \-\-only\-missing
Translate only missing values
.SS config
Manage translation provider configuration.
.PP
.B lrm config
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR
.PP
Subcommands:
.IP \(bu 2
.B list-providers
- List available translation providers
.IP \(bu 2
.B set-key
- Set API key for a provider
.IP \(bu 2
.B show-config
- Display current configuration
.SS chain
Execute multiple LRM commands sequentially in a single invocation.
.PP
.B lrm chain
\fICOMMANDS\fR
[\fB\-\-continue\-on\-error\fR]
[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
.TP
.I COMMANDS
Commands to execute, separated by ' -- ' (space-dash-dash-space)
.TP
.BR \-\-continue\-on\-error
Continue executing commands even if one fails (default: stop on first error)
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Show what commands would be executed without running them
.PP
Examples:
.TP
Translation workflow:
.B lrm chain validate --format json -- translate --only-missing -- export -o output.csv
.TP
Validation and scanning:
.B lrm chain validate -- scan --strict
.TP
Backup before update:
.B lrm chain backup create -- update SaveButton --lang default:"Save" -- validate
.TP
Dry run to preview:
.B lrm chain validate -- translate --only-missing --dry-run
.SH FILES
.TP
.I lrm.json
Configuration file (auto-discovered in resource folder)
.TP
.I ~/.lrm/
User configuration directory
.TP
.I ~/.lrm/translation-cache.db
Translation cache database
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B LRM_GOOGLE_API_KEY
Google Cloud Translation API key
.TP
.B LRM_DEEPL_API_KEY
DeepL API key
.TP
.B LRM_OPENAI_API_KEY
OpenAI API key
.TP
.B LRM_CLAUDE_API_KEY
Anthropic Claude API key
.TP
.B LRM_AZURE_TRANSLATOR_KEY
Azure Translator API key
.TP
.B LRM_AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY
Azure OpenAI API key
.TP
.B DOTNET_CLI_TELEMETRY_OPTOUT
Set to 1 to disable .NET telemetry
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Validate all resource files:
.B lrm validate
.TP
View translation statistics:
.B lrm stats
.TP
Launch interactive editor:
.B lrm edit
.TP
View a specific key:
.B lrm view SaveButton
.TP
View keys matching a pattern:
.B lrm view "Error.*"
.TP
Add a new key interactively:
.B lrm add NewKey \-i
.TP
Translate missing values with Google:
.B lrm translate \-\-only\-missing \-\-provider google \-\-target\-languages fr,de,es
.TP
Export to CSV:
.B lrm export \-o translations.csv
.TP
Scan source code for unused keys:
.B lrm scan \-\-show\-unused
.TP
Create a backup:
.B lrm backup create \-\-description "Before major refactoring"
.TP
List backups:
.B lrm backup list
.TP
Restore from backup:
.B lrm backup restore \-\-version 5 \-\-preview
